1
00:00:19,267 --> 00:00:21,000
I just really want to visit you.

2
00:00:21,067 --> 00:00:22,533
Sorry for leaving you so soon,
Love.

3
00:00:22,600 --> 00:00:24,433
Next time we should go out again
with Tiffany.

4
00:00:24,500 --> 00:00:27,433
I know she still has
a resistance

5
00:00:27,500 --> 00:00:29,000
to our wedding plans.

6
00:00:29,067 --> 00:00:31,200
And I'm willing to wait
when she's ready.

7
00:00:31,267 --> 00:00:33,167
I'm sorry.
My jeep can't be fixed today.

8
00:00:33,233 --> 00:00:34,233
How will we go home?

9
00:00:34,333 --> 00:00:36,667
You can sleep at my house
tonight.

10
00:00:36,733 --> 00:00:37,900
Let's go to sleep.

11
00:00:37,967 --> 00:00:39,767
Where are we going today?

12
00:00:39,833 --> 00:00:41,667
- Paguriran.
- The lagoon?

13
00:00:41,733 --> 00:00:43,700
Is that where the big bats are?

14
00:00:43,767 --> 00:00:45,000
There's something
I will admit to you.

15
00:00:45,067 --> 00:00:47,567
Actually, there's no bats.

16
00:00:47,633 --> 00:00:49,467
I just made that up
when we were kids

17
00:00:49,533 --> 00:00:51,733
so we can be close.

18
00:00:51,800 --> 00:00:53,233
You should forgive Mikoy.

19
00:00:53,300 --> 00:00:55,867
I'm sure he has done
a lot of good things.

20
00:00:55,933 --> 00:00:57,367
He only made a mistake once.

21
00:00:57,433 --> 00:00:59,100
You should forgive him.
What's with you?

22
00:00:59,167 --> 00:01:01,133
I'm annoyed with him.

23
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:03,733
I noticed you're the only one
who is eating.

24
00:01:03,800 --> 00:01:04,933
Why don't you feed Mikoy too?

25
00:01:09,300 --> 00:01:09,667
That's a lot.

26
00:01:11,233 --> 00:01:11,667
Do you want some more fish?

27
00:01:22,100 --> 00:01:25,167
Cuz, let's stay here
for a while.

28
00:01:25,233 --> 00:01:26,933
There will be a drinking session
later.

29
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:29,967
And there will be dancing,
like this.

30
00:01:30,033 --> 00:01:30,767
What a waste if we'll leave...

31
00:01:31,833 --> 00:01:34,933
It looks like Mikoy will ask me
to go home later.

32
00:01:36,367 --> 00:01:38,667
I'll take care of Mikoy.

33
00:01:38,733 --> 00:01:41,000
I'm sure he also wants
to be with you.

34
00:01:41,100 --> 00:01:43,533
Of course, he wants
to make it up to you.

35
00:01:43,600 --> 00:01:44,033
You know.

36
00:01:45,333 --> 00:01:46,433
It's annoying.

37
00:01:46,500 --> 00:01:49,167
It's petty but it's annoying.

38
00:01:50,733 --> 00:01:53,400
Cuz, do you notice something
with Mikoy.

39
00:01:54,867 --> 00:01:56,033
This is just my opinion.

40
00:01:56,100 --> 00:01:59,633
I feel that there's something
with Mikoy.

41
00:02:01,033 --> 00:02:01,900
What do you mean something?

42
00:02:02,900 --> 00:02:04,433
What else?

43
00:02:04,500 --> 00:02:06,100
He still likes you.

44
00:02:06,167 --> 00:02:08,400
May-May,
it's just your imagination.

45
00:02:10,433 --> 00:02:12,500
Plus Mikoy knows
that I'm getting married.

46
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:15,167
He's just helping me
with the community service.

47
00:02:15,233 --> 00:02:15,633
That's it.

48
00:02:17,333 --> 00:02:19,333
I don't know.

49
00:02:19,400 --> 00:02:21,000
I feel something different.

50
00:02:21,067 --> 00:02:22,967
I have a gut feeling.

51
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:27,933
Oh my, anyway,
where is the shower here?

52
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:31,100
It's over there.

53
00:02:33,300 --> 00:02:34,600
- I took a shower there.
- Okay.

54
00:02:36,567 --> 00:02:37,633
Should I come with you?

55
00:02:37,700 --> 00:02:40,233
No, I'm okay. I can manage.

56
00:02:40,300 --> 00:02:41,833
Okay, take care.

57
00:02:41,900 --> 00:02:42,267
Yes.

58
00:02:55,233 --> 00:02:55,700
What's that?

59
00:03:02,633 --> 00:03:03,433
What are you doing?

60
00:03:35,100 --> 00:03:38,133
I won't allow that fool
to sleep beside you.

61
00:03:39,733 --> 00:03:42,333
James, we are together
in the room.

62
00:03:43,833 --> 00:03:46,100
Even though.
I don't trust that guy.

63
00:03:46,167 --> 00:03:47,267
You can't trust that guy.

64
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:50,567
Babe,

65
00:03:51,833 --> 00:03:53,967
Basti is not that type of guy.

66
00:03:54,067 --> 00:03:55,267
Why are you always
defending him?

67
00:03:55,333 --> 00:03:57,067
- I am not.
- Yes, you are.

68
00:03:57,133 --> 00:03:58,933
I'm just being reasonable.

69
00:04:01,267 --> 00:04:02,900
Babe, please don't act
like a child.

70
00:04:02,967 --> 00:04:04,400
We've talked about this already.

71
00:04:04,467 --> 00:04:07,467
I know but sleeping beside him
is not part of the deal.

72
00:04:08,500 --> 00:04:10,500
He might do something to you.

73
00:04:10,567 --> 00:04:11,967
And do you think
I will allow it?

74
00:04:13,367 --> 00:04:16,833
James, can we just stop this?

75
00:04:16,900 --> 00:04:18,800
We've talked about this already.

76
00:04:18,867 --> 00:04:21,200
Besides,
this is not going anywhere.

77
00:04:21,267 --> 00:04:22,933
There you go! Finally,
I was able to send the message.

78
00:04:28,733 --> 00:04:31,533
Sorry, I messaged
Mother and Father.

79
00:04:33,633 --> 00:04:34,900
They might worry.

80
00:04:36,433 --> 00:04:39,133
Wait, are you okay?

81
00:04:39,200 --> 00:04:40,333
Can we go in?

82
00:04:41,933 --> 00:04:43,300
I'll go inside.

83
00:04:45,367 --> 00:04:46,400
Excuse me.

84
00:04:49,667 --> 00:04:50,567
Keep your hands to yourself.

85
00:04:51,967 --> 00:04:53,400
Don't ever think about it.

86
00:04:53,467 --> 00:04:54,200
He's going crazy.

87
00:04:57,100 --> 00:04:58,767
Are you trying to peep?

88
00:04:58,833 --> 00:05:01,333
Oh my God, no. I just arrived.

89
00:05:01,433 --> 00:05:02,100
Why didn't you knock?

90
00:05:03,233 --> 00:05:05,033
Why didn't you lock the door?

91
00:05:06,067 --> 00:05:07,800
I'm not used
to locking the door.

92
00:05:07,867 --> 00:05:09,333
My Grandmother is the only one
with me in the house.

93
00:05:10,733 --> 00:05:12,167
I'm going.

94
00:05:12,233 --> 00:05:12,800
This is sickening.

95
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:15,100
Is it sickening?

96
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:10,467
May I join you?

97
00:06:13,900 --> 00:06:15,867
Will you leave if I say no?

98
00:06:18,367 --> 00:06:19,033
Actually, no.

99
00:06:21,167 --> 00:06:22,633
I asked May-May where you are.

100
00:06:22,700 --> 00:06:23,367
She said you're here.

101
00:06:29,100 --> 00:06:31,400
You know, I'm sorry
for what happened back then.

102
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:37,033
I just did that
because I want you to notice me.

103
00:06:39,733 --> 00:06:42,600
I'm naughty then but you know
that I love you so much.

104
00:06:45,433 --> 00:06:45,900
Even if...

105
00:06:47,900 --> 00:06:51,367
I always tease you,

106
00:06:51,433 --> 00:06:52,133
but you know...

107
00:06:54,533 --> 00:06:56,900
that I won't allow
anyone to hurt you.

108
00:06:58,533 --> 00:06:59,900
Even if I'm the one
who gets hurt

109
00:06:59,967 --> 00:07:00,433
as long as it's not you.

110
00:07:04,433 --> 00:07:05,700
What am I saying?

111
00:07:08,167 --> 00:07:10,267
Well, should I still be ashamed?

112
00:07:12,200 --> 00:07:13,400
You have seen everything in me.

113
00:07:17,033 --> 00:07:20,967
I'm sorry if I walked in
and you were naked.

114
00:07:22,767 --> 00:07:26,433
It's your fault.
You didn't lock the door.

115
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:29,233
I'm not used to locking the door
in the house.

116
00:07:29,300 --> 00:07:30,467
Grandmother Ikay is the only one
with me in the house.

117
00:07:30,533 --> 00:07:32,200
She doesn't go
inside the bathroom.

118
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:36,333
What? I'm sorry.

119
00:07:38,233 --> 00:07:39,467
You know we're quits already.

120
00:07:40,733 --> 00:07:44,767
I fooled you back then
and you saw me naked today,

121
00:07:44,833 --> 00:07:45,900
right? So, it's fair.

122
00:07:46,867 --> 00:07:47,200
Am I right?

123
00:07:51,500 --> 00:07:51,933
What?

124
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:58,100
I'm sorry.

125
00:07:58,167 --> 00:07:59,700
Celeste!

126
00:07:59,767 --> 00:08:00,467
Mikoy!

127
00:08:02,633 --> 00:08:04,567
Hey, hello.

128
00:08:04,633 --> 00:08:05,433
Hello!

129
00:08:08,567 --> 00:08:08,867
Hey.

130
00:08:10,233 --> 00:08:10,933
I'm okay.

131
00:08:12,233 --> 00:08:14,233
May-May, you should drink
slowly.

132
00:08:14,300 --> 00:08:16,533
I have no plans of taking home
two drunk women.

133
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:18,033
Drunk?

134
00:08:18,100 --> 00:08:18,733
Me, drunk?

135
00:08:19,767 --> 00:08:20,867
I'm not drunk.

136
00:08:20,967 --> 00:08:21,633
Who is drunk?

137
00:08:22,967 --> 00:08:23,533
Just kidding.

138
00:08:25,767 --> 00:08:27,633
Come on, let's just dance.

139
00:08:27,700 --> 00:08:30,667
Let's imagine
that there's music.

140
00:08:30,733 --> 00:08:32,000
It's just like this.

141
00:08:33,900 --> 00:08:36,367
Step, step,

142
00:08:36,433 --> 00:08:37,433
dance!

143
00:08:37,500 --> 00:08:38,333
There.

144
00:08:38,400 --> 00:08:40,500
Step, step,

145
00:08:40,567 --> 00:08:41,267
dance!

146
00:08:42,400 --> 00:08:44,467
Step, step,

147
00:08:44,533 --> 00:08:45,867
dance!

148
00:08:45,933 --> 00:08:48,067
Step, step,

149
00:08:48,133 --> 00:08:49,100
dance!

150
00:08:49,167 --> 00:08:52,133
Like that! Step, step,

151
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:53,367
dance!

152
00:08:53,433 --> 00:08:55,533
Step, step,

153
00:08:55,633 --> 00:08:56,867
dance!

154
00:08:56,933 --> 00:08:58,833
Step, step,

155
00:08:58,900 --> 00:09:00,033
dance!

156
00:09:00,100 --> 00:09:00,667
Like that.

157
00:09:01,900 --> 00:09:03,100
Go ahead. Drink some more!

158
00:09:03,167 --> 00:09:05,200
Step, step,

159
00:09:05,267 --> 00:09:05,867
dance!

160
00:09:06,967 --> 00:09:09,033
Step, step,

161
00:09:09,100 --> 00:09:10,367
dance!

162
00:09:10,433 --> 00:09:11,867
Dance, dance!

163
00:09:14,433 --> 00:09:16,500
Step, step,

164
00:09:16,567 --> 00:09:17,367
dance!

165
00:09:18,633 --> 00:09:20,033
Like tha, right?

166
00:09:20,100 --> 00:09:20,733
That's enough.

167
00:09:22,667 --> 00:09:24,133
Come on, let's dance.

168
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:25,967
- What?
- Right?

169
00:09:26,033 --> 00:09:26,933
- Hey!
- Hey!

170
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:28,567
- Wait, are you okay?
- Just kidding.

171
00:09:28,667 --> 00:09:29,267
I'm okay.

172
00:09:30,367 --> 00:09:32,467
Step, step,

173
00:09:32,533 --> 00:09:33,433
dance!
Like that!

174
00:09:37,833 --> 00:09:39,800
I directed you
to the wrong bathroom.

175
00:09:42,333 --> 00:09:43,767
It was Mikoy
who was taking a bath.

176
00:09:48,400 --> 00:09:50,800
Oh, I saw everything.

177
00:09:50,867 --> 00:09:52,700
As in everything?

178
00:09:52,767 --> 00:09:54,333
Yes, in his naked glory.

179
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:56,467
- Without any cover?
- Nothing!

180
00:09:58,567 --> 00:10:00,633
Side A, side B.

181
00:10:00,700 --> 00:10:02,767
You should've brought me along
so I could see it too!

182
00:10:04,567 --> 00:10:04,833
What a pity.

183
00:10:06,100 --> 00:10:08,167
- Do you want that?
- You didn't bring me along.

184
00:10:08,233 --> 00:10:10,367
- What a pity.
- The spirit of alcohol

185
00:10:10,433 --> 00:10:13,200
does something different, right?

186
00:10:13,267 --> 00:10:14,767
Earlier,
you couldn't look at me.

187
00:10:15,900 --> 00:10:17,600
Now, you're talking
as if I don't exist.

188
00:10:18,767 --> 00:10:21,033
- Wait.
- It's him.

189
00:10:21,100 --> 00:10:21,533
Mikoy...

190
00:10:23,367 --> 00:10:24,433
wait, wait.

191
00:10:24,500 --> 00:10:25,000
Time out.

192
00:10:25,967 --> 00:10:28,267
I need to pee I'll just go
to the bathroom.

193
00:10:28,333 --> 00:10:29,733
Is that okay?

194
00:10:29,800 --> 00:10:31,100
You lock the door!

195
00:10:32,433 --> 00:10:34,733
Step, step,

196
00:10:34,833 --> 00:10:35,300
dance!

197
00:10:37,400 --> 00:10:39,067
Step, step,

198
00:10:40,067 --> 00:10:41,200
dance!

199
00:10:43,233 --> 00:10:45,700
Step, step,

200
00:10:45,767 --> 00:10:46,400
dance!

201
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:57,933
Is that what you learned
in Manila,

202
00:10:59,467 --> 00:11:00,633
to be a drunkard?

203
00:11:01,800 --> 00:11:03,333
What's with you?

204
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:05,100
Let your hair down.

205
00:11:05,167 --> 00:11:08,733
It's time to celebrate
your individuality.

206
00:11:08,833 --> 00:11:11,567
I'm not used
to seeing you drunk.

207
00:11:13,333 --> 00:11:14,333
What in this?

208
00:11:15,433 --> 00:11:17,067
Why did I get drunk so quickly?

209
00:11:18,467 --> 00:11:19,100
That was quick.

210
00:11:20,533 --> 00:11:26,633
They say that if you're drunk,
you can say what you want to say

211
00:11:26,700 --> 00:11:28,167
that you can't say
if you're normal.

212
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:32,633
Really?

213
00:11:33,933 --> 00:11:35,267
Okay, game. Let's test that.

214
00:11:39,167 --> 00:11:43,867
Pretend that we didn't part
ways.

215
00:11:43,967 --> 00:11:46,167
Okay, it didn't happen

216
00:11:46,233 --> 00:11:48,433
and Tonito boy didn't come
into my life.

217
00:11:48,500 --> 00:11:50,233
We're still a couple

218
00:11:50,300 --> 00:11:52,167
and I'm like this.

219
00:11:52,233 --> 00:11:55,033
Like this.
Like me and all that jazz.

220
00:11:56,500 --> 00:11:57,933
Will you still love me?

221
00:12:14,767 --> 00:12:15,967
Why can't you answer me?

222
00:13:38,633 --> 00:13:40,333
Okay, I'll switch
the lights off.

223
00:13:41,467 --> 00:13:42,733
Don't.

224
00:13:42,800 --> 00:13:44,067
That can't be.

225
00:13:44,133 --> 00:13:46,900
I can't sleep
if the light is on.

226
00:13:46,967 --> 00:13:48,800
Me too, I can't sleep.

227
00:13:48,867 --> 00:13:50,233
Go ahead Mr. Nanding.

228
00:13:50,300 --> 00:13:51,833
You can switch the lights off.

229
00:13:51,900 --> 00:13:56,067
Anyway, you own the house
and we're just guests here.

230
00:13:56,167 --> 00:13:58,800
Besides you might lack sleep.

231
00:13:58,867 --> 00:14:00,133
That's dangerous.

232
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:02,333
Your blood pressure might go up.

233
00:14:02,400 --> 00:14:04,300
My Father is also like that.

234
00:14:04,367 --> 00:14:06,500
Okay, I'll switch it off.
Let's go to sleep.

235
00:14:06,567 --> 00:14:06,933
Okay.

236
00:14:19,633 --> 00:14:20,567
Mikoy, here.

237
00:14:30,133 --> 00:14:30,500
Mikoy,

238
00:14:32,667 --> 00:14:33,867
is Celeste drunk?

239
00:14:36,700 --> 00:14:39,767
Yes. She and May-May drank
earlier.

240
00:14:39,833 --> 00:14:40,400
Oh my....

241
00:14:41,967 --> 00:14:45,767
Do you have lukewarm
water and a face towel?

242
00:14:45,833 --> 00:14:46,967
I have.

243
00:14:47,033 --> 00:14:48,067
Wait, I'll get it.

244
00:14:48,133 --> 00:14:49,200
Okay.

245
00:14:49,267 --> 00:14:52,900
I'll wake up Adora
to attend to her.

246
00:14:52,967 --> 00:14:54,233
Okay, I'll wait for you.

247
00:14:54,300 --> 00:14:55,000
Just a second.

248
00:15:13,633 --> 00:15:14,267
How are you?

249
00:15:16,033 --> 00:15:18,667
Grandmother is just buying
medicine in town

250
00:15:18,733 --> 00:15:19,400
but she's on her way back.

251
00:15:22,333 --> 00:15:24,067
You still don't want to go home?

252
00:15:28,367 --> 00:15:29,567
Okay, you can stay here.

253
00:15:29,633 --> 00:15:33,333
Here, I brought lukewarm
lemon juice.

254
00:15:33,400 --> 00:15:33,767
You should drink this.

255
00:15:35,867 --> 00:15:36,233
Can you manage?

256
00:15:45,833 --> 00:15:48,333
You know, that's what my Mother
and my Father used to give me

257
00:15:48,400 --> 00:15:50,367
when they were still alive.

258
00:15:50,433 --> 00:15:53,567
Go ahead, drink some more
to get rid of the flu quickly.

259
00:15:57,933 --> 00:15:58,267
Is it delicious?

260
00:16:03,267 --> 00:16:04,367
What?

261
00:16:04,433 --> 00:16:05,233
Do you still feel cold?

262
00:16:08,733 --> 00:16:09,033
Here.

263
00:16:15,333 --> 00:16:19,200
Do you still feel cold?

264
00:16:19,267 --> 00:16:19,700
Not anymore.

265
00:16:23,533 --> 00:16:24,133
Just rest.

266
00:16:25,400 --> 00:16:26,467
Thank you, Mikoy.

267
00:16:28,067 --> 00:16:29,633
You're always taking care of me.

268
00:16:33,033 --> 00:16:34,533
What will happen to me
if you're not around?

269
00:16:38,567 --> 00:16:39,700
I will never neglect you.

270
00:16:40,800 --> 00:16:43,367
I'll just be here by your side
until we get old.

271
00:16:43,467 --> 00:16:43,967
That's my promise.

272
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:46,000
I'll take care of you.

273
00:16:47,533 --> 00:16:48,567
You should rest first.

274
00:16:50,300 --> 00:16:51,000
Do you still feel cold?

275
00:16:59,933 --> 00:17:00,533
If you only knew

276
00:17:02,533 --> 00:17:04,267
how happy I am to see you happy.

277
00:17:09,033 --> 00:17:11,300
I really want to answer
your questions earlier.

278
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:18,400
Especially what if
we're still together?

279
00:17:21,833 --> 00:17:24,300
Then I'll be the happiest man
in the whole world.

280
00:17:55,567 --> 00:17:55,933
Ouch...

281
00:17:59,233 --> 00:17:59,667
What was that?

282
00:18:00,833 --> 00:18:01,967
What happened?

283
00:18:02,033 --> 00:18:02,933
Nothing.

284
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:05,500
- What did you do?
- Nothing happened.

285
00:18:05,567 --> 00:18:06,533
Let me see.

286
00:18:06,600 --> 00:18:08,867
Hey, go look somewhere else.

287
00:18:08,933 --> 00:18:11,200
I'm just concerned.
Maybe an insect with venom

288
00:18:11,267 --> 00:18:12,800
bit her.

289
00:18:12,867 --> 00:18:13,933
Maybe she's not immune to that.

290
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:15,533
She might have an allergy.

291
00:18:15,600 --> 00:18:16,667
You want to touch her,
don't you?

292
00:18:17,900 --> 00:18:19,267
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

293
00:18:19,333 --> 00:18:19,700
Hey...

294
00:18:21,133 --> 00:18:22,767
you should go to sleep.

295
00:18:22,867 --> 00:18:24,467
What are you fighting about?

296
00:18:25,833 --> 00:18:27,300
Go to sleep.

297
00:18:27,367 --> 00:18:27,933
I'm sorry.

298
00:18:30,133 --> 00:18:31,800
Let's go to sleep.

299
00:18:31,867 --> 00:18:35,800
That light is not turning off,

300
00:18:35,867 --> 00:18:36,300
okay?

301
00:18:37,467 --> 00:18:42,233
And you Basti, please stay away.

302
00:18:42,300 --> 00:18:43,500
Where will I go?

303
00:18:43,567 --> 00:18:45,167
There's no space here anymore.

304
00:18:45,233 --> 00:18:47,933
And you Tiffany,
you should turn back.

305
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:49,133
Yes, I will.

306
00:18:49,200 --> 00:18:52,500
But please, don't make trouble.

307
00:18:52,567 --> 00:18:53,833
Please.

308
00:18:55,967 --> 00:18:57,067
- Let's go to sleep.
- James, go to sleep.

309
00:20:18,767 --> 00:20:20,533
Just relax. I'm here.

310
00:20:20,600 --> 00:20:23,367
Mikoy, don't leave me.

311
00:20:23,433 --> 00:20:24,867
I won't leave you, okay?

312
00:20:24,933 --> 00:20:25,400
Come here.

313
00:20:26,467 --> 00:20:28,600
I won't leave you, okay?

314
00:20:39,367 --> 00:20:43,900
Cuz, I noticed that you are
the only one who is eating.

315
00:20:43,967 --> 00:20:45,167
Why don't you feed Mikoy too?

316
00:20:47,033 --> 00:20:47,567
Is that so?

317
00:20:51,567 --> 00:20:52,967
Okay, let's roll this
so it will be delicious.

318
00:20:57,833 --> 00:20:58,200
That's a lot.

319
00:21:01,500 --> 00:21:01,900
Thank you.

320
00:21:05,233 --> 00:21:05,600
Sorry.

321
00:21:07,033 --> 00:21:07,467
Do you want fish?

322
00:21:11,433 --> 00:21:11,900
Delicious.

323
00:21:19,400 --> 00:21:19,967
What are you doing?

324
00:21:25,200 --> 00:21:30,033
Let's pretend
that we didn't part ways.

325
00:21:30,100 --> 00:21:32,200
Okay, it didn't happen

326
00:21:32,267 --> 00:21:34,467
and Tonito boy didn't come
into my life.

327
00:21:34,533 --> 00:21:35,167
We're still a couple

328
00:21:36,333 --> 00:21:37,267
and I'm like this.

329
00:21:38,267 --> 00:21:41,033
Like this, like me
and all that jazz.

330
00:21:42,600 --> 00:21:44,033
Will you still love me?

331
00:22:57,400 --> 00:23:00,500
Oh my gosh, my head hurts.

332
00:23:01,667 --> 00:23:02,800
There you go.

333
00:23:04,600 --> 00:23:06,800
Celeste, you're awake.

334
00:23:06,867 --> 00:23:09,733
Your Auntie Adora
prepared breakfast for you.

335
00:23:09,800 --> 00:23:11,967
She cooked you Arroz Caldo.

336
00:23:12,033 --> 00:23:13,100
Are you going to eat?

337
00:23:13,167 --> 00:23:14,800
Ouch. My head hurts.

338
00:23:14,867 --> 00:23:17,167
I drank a bit too much
yesterday.

339
00:23:17,233 --> 00:23:19,700
You know Celeste,
Mikoy just came home.

340
00:23:20,633 --> 00:23:21,933
He watched over you
the whole night.

341
00:23:24,033 --> 00:23:25,567
Did he change my clothes?

342
00:23:25,633 --> 00:23:27,567
Of course not.

343
00:23:27,633 --> 00:23:29,400
Your Auntie Adora did that.

344
00:23:29,467 --> 00:23:32,333
But Mikoy didn't leave you.

345
00:23:34,033 --> 00:23:35,300
What?

346
00:23:35,367 --> 00:23:36,600
You should eat the porridge.

347
00:23:36,667 --> 00:23:38,667
Just in time, it's still hot.

348
00:23:38,733 --> 00:23:40,633
I just put it there.

349
00:23:40,700 --> 00:23:43,867
Father, I don't eat carbs.

350
00:23:45,500 --> 00:23:47,400
But can you scoop the egg?

351
00:23:47,467 --> 00:23:49,333
I'll have the protein instead.

352
00:23:50,967 --> 00:23:52,033
Just egg?

353
00:23:52,100 --> 00:23:54,033
Okay, Celeste, I'll do that.

354
00:23:54,100 --> 00:23:54,700
Just egg.

355
00:24:09,467 --> 00:24:12,433
Why are you ignoring my calls
and messages?

356
00:24:16,533 --> 00:24:17,333
Tonito,

357
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:20,367
are you still mad at me?

358
00:24:23,900 --> 00:24:25,000
I don't think
this is the right time

359
00:24:25,067 --> 00:24:26,200
to talk about that, Aurelia.

360
00:24:27,500 --> 00:24:28,800
I'm sorry.

361
00:24:28,900 --> 00:24:30,300
I shouldn't have done that.

362
00:24:31,267 --> 00:24:32,067
I know it's not...

363
00:24:33,233 --> 00:24:33,567
right

364
00:24:35,167 --> 00:24:39,433
but maybe it's just part
of my frailties being a woman.

365
00:24:40,667 --> 00:24:41,500
You know what I mean.

366
00:24:46,200 --> 00:24:47,700
I don't want to be rude to you,
Aurelia.

367
00:24:49,367 --> 00:24:50,167
I respect you

368
00:24:51,233 --> 00:24:52,600
and I don't want
you to lose that.

369
00:24:55,600 --> 00:24:56,933
You'll have to excuse me.

370
00:25:10,233 --> 00:25:11,767
Last night was terrible.

371
00:25:11,833 --> 00:25:13,667
I'm so wasted.

372
00:25:13,733 --> 00:25:15,067
I drank a lot.

373
00:25:15,133 --> 00:25:17,600
- Too much.
- My head hurts.

374
00:25:17,667 --> 00:25:21,167
You don't remember
what you did and said?

375
00:25:21,233 --> 00:25:22,133
Wait, what?
What did I say?

376
00:25:24,167 --> 00:25:26,833
Wait, are you the one
who dressed me?

377
00:25:26,900 --> 00:25:28,667
Did I dance on the table?

378
00:25:28,733 --> 00:25:29,400
I danced...

379
00:25:30,700 --> 00:25:32,133
did I say something distasteful?

380
00:25:33,267 --> 00:25:35,967
- More likely naughty.
- More?

381
00:25:36,067 --> 00:25:39,300
- Naughty?
- No, more like kinky.

382
00:25:39,367 --> 00:25:40,800
Kinky?

383
00:25:40,867 --> 00:25:43,067
- No.
- You shouldn't drink too much.

384
00:25:43,133 --> 00:25:44,700
Look, you did some outrageous
things

385
00:25:45,767 --> 00:25:46,467
but I didn't look.

386
00:25:48,300 --> 00:25:52,833
Can I possibly be absent
from the community service?

387
00:25:52,900 --> 00:25:56,433
It's like I don't feel well.

388
00:25:56,500 --> 00:25:58,067
It's like I have a fever.

389
00:25:58,133 --> 00:25:59,833
- There's your drama again.
- It's true.

390
00:25:59,900 --> 00:26:01,100
- Check it.
- You're hot?

391
00:26:02,167 --> 00:26:03,300
I'm hot.

392
00:26:03,367 --> 00:26:04,867
You're not hot today.

393
00:26:04,933 --> 00:26:06,167
You were hot last night.

394
00:26:07,667 --> 00:26:09,800
Mikoy, what's with you?

395
00:26:09,900 --> 00:26:11,033
Don't be like that.

396
00:26:25,967 --> 00:26:28,133
Those dimples of yours,
that's where I fell in love.

397
00:26:29,433 --> 00:26:32,267
You know you will miss me
when I go back to Manila.

398
00:26:32,333 --> 00:26:34,667
For sure I'll miss
you're being a troublemaker.

399
00:26:34,733 --> 00:26:36,333
And what you say
when you're drunk.

400
00:26:36,400 --> 00:26:37,800
Hey...

401
00:26:37,867 --> 00:26:40,167
Celeste is really
very beautiful.

402
00:26:40,233 --> 00:26:43,367
Tell me that you're not in love
with her.

403
00:26:43,467 --> 00:26:44,933
There's nobody there.

404
00:26:45,000 --> 00:26:48,467
Do you know where Mikoy
and Grandmother Ikay are?

405
00:26:48,533 --> 00:26:50,133
You're jealous.

406
00:26:50,200 --> 00:26:52,533
Because I see something
to be jealous of.

407
00:26:52,600 --> 00:26:53,800
It looks like
you're enjoying it.

408
00:26:53,867 --> 00:26:56,900
I heard that they will make
a secret recipe.

409
00:26:56,967 --> 00:27:00,667
My only secret in cooking
is being happy.

410
00:27:00,733 --> 00:27:03,033
Have you seen Grandmother Ikay
and Mikoy?

411
00:27:03,100 --> 00:27:03,867
They are inside.

412
00:27:05,100 --> 00:27:05,400
Mikoy?

413
00:27:06,400 --> 00:27:06,900
Hazel.
